message.content: The paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and conversation modeling. Other likely sub-categories could be "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves neural models and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it involves training and evaluating models. "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) and "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) could also be possible sub-categories as the paper deals with generating questions in a conversational context and involves modeling conversation flow.
